---
// src/components/EssayBreak.astro
//
// The asterism divider (⁂) — a typographic ornament marking a stronger
// pause than a paragraph break or an in-body `---` (which we render
// invisibly). Used at the end of an essay to separate the body from
// the footnote apparatus, with optional editorial content (e.g. a
// photo credit line) sitting between this and <FootnotesHeading />.
//
// Authoring shape in MDX:
//
//   ...essay body ends.
//
//   <EssayBreak />
//
//   *Photos here are by me and Shreya. Thank you, S.*
//
//   <FootnotesHeading />
//
//   <Footnote id="1">First footnote.</Footnote>
//
// If there's no editorial content between the break and the heading,
// just write them back-to-back — the spacing is tuned to look right
// in either case.
//
// Replaced the previous <FootnoteSection /> component (April 2026),
// which rendered both the asterism AND the "Footnotes" label as a
// single block. Splitting allows arbitrary editorial prose
// (acknowledgments, photo credits, dedications) to live between them
// in MDX, where the author has full typographic control.
//
// Styles for .essay-asterism live in EssayLayout.astro's <style is:global>
// block; this component contributes only the markup.
---

<div class="essay-asterism" role="separator" aria-hidden="true">⁂</div>
